<div>A Geiger tube is a</div><div><ul><li>Sealed metal tube containing&nbsp;<b>argon gas at low pressure</b>.</li><li>The&nbsp;<b>thin mica window</b>&nbsp;at the end of the tube to allow&nbsp;\(\alpha\)&nbsp;and&nbsp;\(\beta\)&nbsp;particles to enter.</li><li>A&nbsp;<b>metal rod</b>&nbsp;down the middle of the tube at a positive potential.</li><li>The&nbsp;<b>tube walls</b>&nbsp;connected to the negative termial of the power supply.</li></ul></div>